==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enantiomorphous
<hw>E*nan`ti*o*mor"phous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'enanti`os</grk> opposite + <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Similar, but not superposable, <it>i.
e.</it>, related to each other as a right-handed to a left-handed glove;
-- said of certain hemihedral crystals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enantiopathic</ent>⟦br⟧
